The `DotGlobeHero` component is a React component designed to display a dynamic, animated globe as a background for hero sections. It utilizes `react-three-fiber` and `react-three-drei` to render a 3D globe with a wireframe effect.

## Key Exports

*   **`DotGlobeHero`**: The main React component for the globe hero. It accepts several props to customize its appearance and behavior.
*   **`DotGlobeHeroProps`**: An interface defining the props available for the `DotGlobeHero` component.

## Props

*   **`rotationSpeed`** (optional, default: `0.005`): Controls the speed of the globe's rotation.
*   **`globeRadius`** (optional, default: `1`): Sets the radius of the globe.
*   **`className`** (optional): Allows for additional CSS classes to be applied to the main container.
*   **`children`** (optional): Any React nodes to be rendered inside the hero section, above the globe.

## Usage Example

```tsx
import { DotGlobeHero } from '@/components/ui/globe-hero';

const MyHeroSection = () => {
  return (
    <DotGlobeHero rotationSpeed={0.01} globeRadius={1.5} className="text-white">
      <h1 className="text-5xl font-bold">Welcome to DocMed</h1>
      <p className="mt-4 text-xl">Your ultimate documentation solution.</p>
    </DotGlobeHero>
  );
};

export default MyHeroSection;
```

